Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.87,0:08:20.08,Chn,,0,0,0,,嘿, 最近怎么样? - Oh, 还好, 没什么事-\N{\rEng}Hey, what's going on? - Oh, not much, just hanging around-
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.11,0:08:24.21,Chn,,0,0,0,,嘿, 耳朵好漂漂呀 大饼脸!\N{\rEng}Hey, nice nice ears. Pizza Face!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.61,0:08:29.19,Chn,,0,0,0,,Butters, 这样可不对 他不能决定自己长什么样\N{\rEng}Butters, that's not cool, man. He can't help how he looks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.32,0:08:37.10,Chn,,0,0,0,,Kyle, 我有个小小建议 也许你应该...\N{\rEng}Kyle, I was going to suggest that maybe you should...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.13,0:08:39.69,Chn,,0,0,0,,和学校里其他丑孩子一起玩\N{\rEng}hang out with the other ugly kids in the school.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.72,0:08:43.61,Chn,,0,0,0,,因为如果你和他们在一起, 你就不那么显眼了 对吧?\N{\rEng}Because if you hang out with them, you won't stand out so much. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.99,0:08:45.23,Chn,,0,0,0,,酷.\N{\rEng}Cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.84,0:09:03.86,Chn,,0,0,0,,嘿.\N{\rEng}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.51,0:09:06.57,Chn,,0,0,0,,你好\N{\rEng}Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.22,0:09:13.22,Chn,,0,0,0,,你还吃你的泡菜吗?\N{\rEng}Are you going to eat your pickle?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.85,0:09:46.88,Chn,,0,0,0,,谁去把足球捡回来? 就在那些丑孩子旁边\N{\rEng}Could somebody toss the football back? It's over there next to the ugly kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.86,0:09:53.66,Chn,,0,0,0,,我憎恨上学 这让我感到很愤怒\N{\rEng}I hate coming to this school. It makes me angry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.90,0:09:54.94,Chn,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.35,0:10:01.13,Chn,,0,0,0,,有时我真想把学校给烧了 烧得一干二净!\N{\rEng}Sometimes I just want to burn it down. Burn the whole school down to the ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.81,0:10:05.90,Chn,,0,0,0,,不 你错了 大错特错!我们不丑!\N{\rEng}No. You know what? Screw this! We aren't ugly!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.93,0:10:07.71,Chn,,0,0,0,,我们不丑? - 一点也不!\N{\rEng}We're not? - No!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.74,0:10:12.11,Chn,,0,0,0,,也许我们只是需要改变一点形象 就是化化妆之类的\N{\rEng}Maybe we all just need a little image change, you know? Like a makeover.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.14,0:10:13.47,Chn,,0,0,0,,好像是\N{\rEng}Hey yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.50,0:10:16.38,Chn,,0,0,0,,比如你! 可能你只需要把头发压一压\N{\rEng}Like you! Maybe you just need to let your hair down.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.42,0:10:18.98,Chn,,0,0,0,,再试试不戴眼镜会看起来怎么样\N{\rEng}And let's see how you look without those glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.50,0:10:28.70,Chn,,0,0,0,,还是戴上吧\N{\rEng}Let's just put those back on.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.49,0:10:42.12,Chn,,0,0,0,,我知道,那首歌实在是太屌了\N{\rEng}I know, that song is so awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.80,0:10:47.32,Chn,,0,0,0,,Wendy. 能跟你说句话么? - 当然, Stan.\N{\rEng}Wendy. Could I talk to you? - Of course, Stan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.35,0:10:49.53,Chn,,0,0,0,,就一分钟 去那吧\N{\rEng}Just for a minute. Over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.80,0:10:53.62,Chn,,0,0,0,,你说他们是不是要和好了?\N{\rEng}You think he's gonna beg her to come back to him?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.30,0:10:57.57,Chn,,0,0,0,,真让我吃惊 我还以为 你再也不和我说话了呢\N{\rEng}This is a nice surprise. I thought you were never speaking to me again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.60,0:11:00.29,Chn,,0,0,0,,唔 我想跟你谈谈你们统计的那个排名\N{\rEng}Yeah well, I wanna talk to you about this list you girls made.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.31,0:11:02.00,Chn,,0,0,0,,哪个排名? 我们统计了很多排名\N{\rEng}Which one? We make lists all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.02,0:11:03.96,Chn,,0,0,0,,关于男生长相的那个\N{\rEng}The one where you rated the boys looks in the class.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.99,0:11:07.37,Chn,,0,0,0,,它对Kyle的打击太大了, okay? 你们怎么会都觉得他丑?\N{\rEng}Look, it really messed Kyle up, okay? How could you vote him the ugliest?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.41,0:11:09.51,Chn,,0,0,0,,说真的 我个人并没投他的票\N{\rEng}Look, personally, I didn't vote him the ugliest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.51,0:11:12.43,Chn,,0,0,0,,我投的是 Eric Cartman 但是 一定有很多其他的女生觉得他-\N{\rEng}My vote was for Eric Cartman. But enough of the other girls must have felt he was-
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.43,0:11:14.91,Chn,,0,0,0,,你也这么觉得吧 也许你们可以修改一下排名\N{\rEng}So it was unanimous. Maybe you can just change the list.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.94,0:11:18.16,Chn,,0,0,0,,修改排名?! 你知道那意味着什么吗?!\N{\rEng}Change the list?! Do you have any idea what that would take?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.19,0:11:21.00,Chn,,0,0,0,,你根本不明白 排名对女生来说有多重要!\N{\rEng}Maybe you don't understand how important list-making is to girls!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.02,0:11:23.92,Chn,,0,0,0,,那可不是什么随随便便的东西! 我们有严格的制度!\N{\rEng}It's just not something we do flippantly! There's protocol!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.95,0:11:28.63,Chn,,0,0,0,,我们能不能问问其她的女生们 为什么她们都把Kyle排在老末儿?\N{\rEng}Can't we just talk to all the girls who made the list and find out why they voted Kyle last?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.67,0:11:34.67,Chn,,0,0,0,,好吧 我会尽力让你能参加下一个排名大会 但你不要抱太大希望\N{\rEng}All right, I'll try and get you into our next list-making meeting. But it won't be easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.54,0:11:43.95,Chn,,0,0,0,,我宣布 今天的排名大会 现在开始 Rebecca 请你发言\N{\rEng}Today's list meeting is called to order. Rebecca, you have the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.98,0:11:48.44,Chn,,0,0,0,,如果大家都没有异议的话 我建议继续讨论第47D号排名:\N{\rEng}If it pleases and sparkles I suggest we continue deliberations on List 47D:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.47,0:11:50.41,Chn,,0,0,0,,"哪位女生 拥有最可爱的钱包"\N{\rEng}Which Girl Has The Cutest Purse?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.43,0:11:54.66,Chn,,0,0,0,,Rebecca 提议继续第47D号排名 大家都同意么?\N{\rEng}Rebecca moves we work on List 47D. Does that sparkle with all the girls?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.69,0:11:55.99,Chn,,0,0,0,,同意\N{\rEng}Sunshine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.09,0:11:59.77,Chn,,0,0,0,,开始讨论"哪位女生 拥有最可爱的钱包"? Milly 发言\N{\rEng}Deliberating "Which Girl Has The Cutest Purse"? Milly has the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.19,0:12:01.52,Chn,,0,0,0,,如果大家都没有异议的话\N{\rEng}If it pleases and sparkles,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.52,0:12:04.16,Chn,,0,0,0,,我认为Jennifer的钱包 可以说是最可爱的\N{\rEng}I would like to submit that Jennifer's purse is by far the cutest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.16,0:12:06.09,Chn,,0,0,0,,绝对要比Teresa的钱包可爱\N{\rEng}Definitely cuter than Teresa's.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.12,0:12:09.73,Chn,,0,0,0,,我认为在座的各位都不反对 Jennifer的钱包比Teresa的可爱\N{\rEng}I don't think anyone here disagrees that Jennifer's purse is cuter than Teresa's,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.73,0:12:11.22,Chn,,0,0,0,,但那并不代表她的是最可爱的\N{\rEng}but it doesn't make it the cutest.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.24,0:12:16.64,Chn,,0,0,0,,委员会已经决定了 有条纹的钱包都不能进入前5名\N{\rEng}The committee has already decided that nothing with stripes can be in the Top 5 cutest purses.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.68,0:12:19.41,Chn,,0,0,0,,下一个请Wendy发言\N{\rEng}Sunshine sparkle Wendy has the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.75,0:12:23.03,Chn,,0,0,0,,如果大家都没有异议 我建议我们重新...\N{\rEng}If it pleases and sparkles, I would like to suggest that we...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.80,0:12:28.16,Chn,,0,0,0,,重新讨论上星期的排名 - 她说什么? 她在开玩笑吧!\N{\rEng}That we reopen last week's list for debate. - What'd she say? She's gotta be kidding!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.21,0:12:30.02,Chn,,0,0,0,,她疯了?\N{\rEng}Is she crazy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.05,0:12:33.01,Chn,,0,0,0,,好吧 请站到主席台前\N{\rEng}All right, come before the Rainbow Railing.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.37,0:12:35.62,Chn,,0,0,0,,说啊\N{\rEng}Go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.23,0:12:40.07,Chn,,0,0,0,,我觉得 你们表决最丑的男生时 是不是有点轻率?\N{\rEng}I was just thinking that maybe you voted a little hastily on the cutest boy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.10,0:12:42.48,Chn,,0,0,0,,你觉得你应该是第一? - 我没说\N{\rEng}You thought you should be number one? - No.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.51,0:12:46.16,Chn,,0,0,0,,我向你保证 我们委员会 从未轻率地对待过任何一个排名!\N{\rEng}Let me assure you that no list is made hastily by this committee!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.19,0:12:50.68,Chn,,0,0,0,,他不是那个意思 他只是想让我们重新讨论一下\N{\rEng}He didn't mean that. He was just saying maybe we should open it up again for discussion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.71,0:12:53.99,Chn,,0,0,0,,根据排名法 我不能举行一场旧排名研讨会\N{\rEng}I cannot by Sparkle Law move to have an old list investigated.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.01,0:12:57.85,Chn,,0,0,0,,但是 如果你能找到调查的必要性 Wendy 我们会考虑的\N{\rEng}However, if you can find recourse for such an inquiry, Wendy, I would review it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.88,0:12:59.83,Chn,,0,0,0,,姐妹们 你们都同意吗?\N{\rEng}Does that sparkle with all the girls?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.87,0:13:01.15,Chn,,0,0,0,,同意\N{\rEng}Sunshine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.98,0:13:10.80,Chn,,0,0,0,,所有人都嘲笑我!\N{\rEng}They all laugh at me!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.84,0:13:15.50,Chn,,0,0,0,,女生们在我背后窃笑! 甚至都不愿意看我一眼\N{\rEng}And the girls giggle behind my back! Unable to even glance at my disfigured face.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.78,0:13:19.01,Chn,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不要放火烧学校 Kyle{\i0}\N{\rEng}{\i1}Do not burn down the school, Kyle.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.81,0:13:22.28,Chn,,0,0,0,,谁在说话? - 是我\N{\rEng}Who said that? - I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.96,0:13:29.10,Chn,,0,0,0,,你知道我是谁吗? - 林肯?\N{\rEng}Do you know who I am? - Abraham Lincoln?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.30,0:13:35.85,Chn,,0,0,0,,在下就是亚伯拉罕· 林肯 放火烧学校是不能解决你的问题的\N{\rEng}I am Abraham Lincoln. Burning down the school will not solve your problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.88,0:13:38.84,Chn,,0,0,0,,你觉得上天对你不公平 因为你生来丑陋\N{\rEng}You think you've been cheated because you are ugly,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.84,0:13:44.54,Chn,,0,0,0,,可是我将使你看到事情的另一面 快来! 有很多地方要去\N{\rEng}but I am here to show you otherwise. Come! There is much to see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.88,0:13:48.11,Chn,,0,0,0,,请你看看这儿\N{\rEng}I want you to look in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.27,0:13:50.40,Chn,,0,0,0,,这位女士是 Nancy Pinkerton.\N{\rEng}This woman is Nancy Pinkerton.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.43,0:13:55.57,Chn,,0,0,0,,她小时候是全校公认最漂亮的女生\N{\rEng}As a child she was consistently the most beautiful girl in her entire school.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.60,0:13:59.83,Chn,,0,0,0,,她的青年时期充满了奉承 生活一帆风顺\N{\rEng}Her life as a youth was filled with praises and everything being handed to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.86,0:14:04.03,Chn,,0,0,0,,男生们跟她说 “你很特殊 你很有趣 你很漂亮”\N{\rEng}Boys told her she was special. She was funny. She was interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.07,0:14:06.53,Chn,,0,0,0,,其实只是因为他们想跟她上床\N{\rEng}But that's only because she was hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.56,0:14:11.14,Chn,,0,0,0,,一直到她40岁 当她的美貌开始消褪时\N{\rEng}It wasn't until she reached age 40, when her looks started to fade,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.17,0:14:16.59,Chn,,0,0,0,,她才发现自己的“特殊、漂亮” 其实只是一些泡沫\N{\rEng}that she learned she was actually about as interesting and special, as a wet carrot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.62,0:14:21.92,Chn,,0,0,0,,这是你的丑朋友 Yamal的家\N{\rEng}This is the home of your new ugly friend, Yamal.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.95,0:14:24.93,Chn,,0,0,0,,因为长得丑 他总是被冷落\N{\rEng}Because he's ugly, he gets nothing handed to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.96,0:14:27.80,Chn,,0,0,0,,所以他不懈努力来实现自己的价值\N{\rEng}He has to work at making something of himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.83,0:14:30.71,Chn,,0,0,0,,当他长大成人后 他的努力将使他受益匪浅\N{\rEng}But that work is gonna pay off when he's an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.74,0:14:35.36,Chn,,0,0,0,,他会有坚韧不拔的品质 而漂亮孩子很少会那样\N{\rEng}He will have character, something that kids who are hot rarely develop.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.39,0:14:37.37,Chn,,0,0,0,,就像你同学 Clyde.\N{\rEng}Like your classmate, Clyde.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.40,0:14:42.06,Chn,,0,0,0,,他知道自己长得帅以后 就不再努力了\N{\rEng}Now that he knows he's good-looking, he doesn't have to make any effort to be special.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.10,0:14:45.83,Chn,,0,0,0,,不是啦 Rebecca只是普通的朋友 我只想和你好\N{\rEng}No, Rebecca's just a friend. I wanna be with you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.13,0:14:48.19,Chn,,0,0,0,,好啊 我当然会给你买几双新鞋\N{\rEng}Sure, yeah, I'll buy you some shoes too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.22,0:14:50.81,Chn,,0,0,0,,从此 他的生活只是泡妞\N{\rEng}Now his life will be about girls.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.84,0:14:53.78,Chn,,0,0,0,,把时间浪费在给女生打电话上 然后给她们买鞋子\N{\rEng}Chatting with them on the phone and buying them shoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.82,0:14:56.00,Chn,,0,0,0,,他很可能早早就结婚了\N{\rEng}He will most likely marry very young,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.03,0:15:00.27,Chn,,0,0,0,,然后直到40岁 才发现自己其实是个傻B\N{\rEng}and not realize until age 40 that he's a total douche.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.31,0:15:05.16,Chn,,0,0,0,,现在你明白了 Kyle 长得漂亮的孩子 其实是很可悲的\N{\rEng}And so you see, Kyle, it is actually the beautiful kids that are cursed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.19,0:15:08.88,Chn,,0,0,0,,我可不想等到长大了才开始快乐 那实在太遥远了\N{\rEng}But I can't wait to be an adult to be happy. That's forever from now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.91,0:15:11.58,Chn,,0,0,0,,要有耐心 - 快把我送回家吧!\N{\rEng}You must be patient. - Just take me home!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.61,0:15:13.96,Chn,,0,0,0,,我不想在这待着了! 送我回家!\N{\rEng}I don't wanna be here anymore! Take me home!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.75,0:15:16.21,Chn,,0,0,0,,哎 好吧\N{\rEng}Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.27,0:15:24.69,Chn,,0,0,0,,Kyle 你需要好好想想我对你说的话\N{\rEng}Kyle, you need to think about what I've told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.73,0:15:28.53,Chn,,0,0,0,,我不! 我不想任何人教我怎么思考问题!\N{\rEng}I don't want to! I don't want anybody telling me how to feel anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.56,0:15:31.23,Chn,,0,0,0,,那你他妈的就是个垃圾!\N{\rEng}Well then you're just a fucking asshole!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.42,0:15:40.34,Chn,,0,0,0,,等等 Stan 我想我发现了一些东西!\N{\rEng}Wait a minute. Wait, Stan, I think I've got something!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.37,0:15:44.23,Chn,,0,0,0,,看这里: 在上次的最帅男生投票中\N{\rEng}Take a look at this: during final deliberation of the list for cutest boy,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.23,0:15:48.00,Chn,,0,0,0,,七个女生才有一个评给Clyde一颗星\N{\rEng}seven girls gave Clyde a glitter rating of only one sparkle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.03,0:15:51.24,Chn,,0,0,0,,我一点也不知道你在说什么 - 数对不上\N{\rEng}I have no idea what you're talking about. - It doesn't add up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.27,0:15:53.46,Chn,,0,0,0,,很可能是Rebecca 统计选票的时候\N{\rEng}It is possible that Rebecca made a mistake
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.46,0:15:56.64,Chn,,0,0,0,,出了一点错\N{\rEng}when she tallied the sunshine votes onto the final list.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.47,0:16:00.86,Chn,,0,0,0,,噢 嘿 Wendy.\N{\rEng}Oh, hey Wendy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.88,0:16:04.76,Chn,,0,0,0,,嘿 Rebecca 你还留着给男生长相排名的投票么?\N{\rEng}Hey Rebecca. Do you still have the voter cards for the list that rated the boys looks?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.80,0:16:07.11,Chn,,0,0,0,,Wendy 我们已经结束那个排名了\N{\rEng}Wendy, we're done with that list.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.14,0:16:09.30,Chn,,0,0,0,,我知道 可我好像发现了一点错误\N{\rEng}I know, but I think there's been a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.32,0:16:12.28,Chn,,0,0,0,,我询问过的女生中 有6个都没选Clyde最帅\N{\rEng}Six of the girls I've talked to didn't vote Clyde the cutest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.31,0:16:14.04,Chn,,0,0,0,,从数学的角度看他根本不可能-\N{\rEng}That means that mathematically he should have been-
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.04,0:16:18.30,Chn,,0,0,0,,停一下 不要再追究下去了!\N{\rEng}All right, you need to stop. Digging. Around, Wendy!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.72,0:16:22.00,Chn,,0,0,0,,你不会喜欢你调查的结果的!\N{\rEng}You might not like what you find!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.04,0:16:25.68,Chn,,0,0,0,,放弃吧 不要再追问了!\N{\rEng}Just back off and stop asking questions!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.71,0:16:31.59,Chn,,0,0,0,,你正在接近一个会使你陷入危险的秘密! 停手吧!\N{\rEng}You're getting close to a secret that I don't think you can handle! Let it go!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.91,0:16:37.93,Chn,,0,0,0,,她好像不太爽, 是么?\N{\rEng}That didn't sparkle with her, did it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.94,0:16:47.52,Chn,,0,0,0,,一罐丙烷 六桶燃油\N{\rEng}One canister of propane, six cans of lighter fluid,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.55,0:16:52.93,Chn,,0,0,0,,七加仑高热煤油 和一盒火柴\N{\rEng}seven gallons of high-octane kerosene and a box of matches.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.15,0:16:57.88,Chn,,0,0,0,,Okay 就这些吗 小伙子? - 这些应该足够了\N{\rEng}Okay, is that everything, little boy? - That should just about do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.91,0:17:00.95,Chn,,0,0,0,,你有积分卡么?\N{\rEng}Do you like to put this on your True-Value card today?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.57,0:17:03.42,Chn,,0,0,0,,尊敬的主席、秘书长\N{\rEng}Honorary Chair, Mrs. Secretary,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.42,0:17:06.82,Chn,,0,0,0,,我相信 有位委员对一份排名动了手脚\N{\rEng}I believe a member of our committee has tampered with one of our lists.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.85,0:17:11.16,Chn,,0,0,0,,根据我的调查和计算 发现Clyde不可能被选为最帅的男生\N{\rEng}I've compiled a full report and it turns out that nobody voted Clude the cutest in the class.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.19,0:17:15.57,Chn,,0,0,0,,我相信 是Rebecca改动了名单 使他成为第一\N{\rEng}I believe Rebecca changed the list to make him number one.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.60,0:17:18.30,Chn,,0,0,0,,她为什么那样做呢? - 排名一出来\N{\rEng}Why would she do that? - Right after the list was made,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.30,0:17:21.93,Chn,,0,0,0,,Rebecca就开始和Clyde约会 这其中是不是有什么联系?\N{\rEng}Rebecca started going out with Clyde. You can read all the discrepancies here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.94,0:17:24.51,Chn,,0,0,0,,我们应该重新制定那份排名\N{\rEng}We need to remake that list.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.49,0:17:31.17,Chn,,0,0,0,,你就是要钻牛角尖!\N{\rEng}You just couldn't let it go!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.74,0:17:36.35,Chn,,0,0,0,,什么意思? 我们应该召集女生们 - 恐怕不行 Wendy!\N{\rEng}What do you mean? Call the girls in. - I'm afraid we can't do that, Wendy!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.69,0:17:40.60,Chn,,0,0,0,,你知道吗 Wendy Clyde的爸爸是镇上精品鞋店的老板?\N{\rEng}Did you know, Wendy, that Clyde's father own the shoe store at the mall?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.71,0:17:43.62,Chn,,0,0,0,,很多女生都想和Clyde约会 来得到新鞋\N{\rEng}A lot of us have always wanted to date Clyde to get free shoes,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.62,0:17:46.85,Chn,,0,0,0,,但我们不能 因为他不够受欢迎\N{\rEng}but we couldn't, because he wasn't popular enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.07,0:17:49.54,Chn,,0,0,0,,你们故意的!\N{\rEng}You knew!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.68,0:17:53.17,Chn,,0,0,0,,不幸的是 Clyde被选为倒数第5!\N{\rEng}Unfortunately, the members voted Clyde in the bottom five of the list!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.20,0:17:58.88,Chn,,0,0,0,,所以我们暗箱操作 打造出一份新的排名 把真的 藏起来\N{\rEng}That's why we had to manipulate the votes, forge a new list and hide the real one!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.96,0:18:02.94,Chn,,0,0,0,,然后你们就可以光明正大的和Clyde约会 让他买鞋?!\N{\rEng}So that you all could justify dating Clyde and get shoes?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.97,0:18:05.44,Chn,,0,0,0,,你们怎么能这样滥用权力!\N{\rEng}How dare you take advantage of your position!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.47,0:18:08.96,Chn,,0,0,0,,我要告诉Bebe 让你们俩都从委员会除名!\N{\rEng}I'm gonna tell Bebe and have you both disbarred from the list committee!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.36,0:18:12.64,Chn,,0,0,0,,Bebe?! 你以为这是谁想出来的计划?!\N{\rEng}Bebe?! Who do you think authorized the buyout?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.50,0:18:16.80,Chn,,0,0,0,,不 不要是她\N{\rEng}No. Not Bebe.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.83,0:18:20.42,Chn,,0,0,0,,她开始和Clyde约会了 她爱死精品鞋了\N{\rEng}She's dating Clyde now. Nobody loves shoes more than her.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.34,0:18:22.36,Chn,,0,0,0,,什么情况?\N{\rEng}What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.36,0:18:24.84,Chn,,0,0,0,,当其他人发现你们篡改投票 她们会-\N{\rEng}When the other girls find out you ignored their votes, they're gonna-
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.84,0:18:27.64,Chn,,0,0,0,,她们会相信你 而不信委员会的领导们?!\N{\rEng}Do you really think they'll believe you over the heads of the committee?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.65,0:18:30.88,Chn,,0,0,0,,我们只要随便搞一个新的名单! "最大的骗子"!\N{\rEng}We'll simple generate a new list! "Biggest Liars"!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.91,0:18:32.59,Chn,,0,0,0,,然后把你排在第一!\N{\rEng}And put you at the top!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.62,0:18:37.26,Chn,,0,0,0,,考虑一下你自己吧 Wendy! 停手吧! 然后闭上你的小嘴!\N{\rEng}Do yourself a favor, Wendy! Just let it go! And keep your little mouth shut!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.59,0:18:38.99,Chn,,0,0,0,,我看不会的!\N{\rEng}I don't think so!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.27,0:18:41.64,Chn,,0,0,0,,Stan,跑!\N{\rEng}Stan, run!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.84,0:18:43.22,Chn,,0,0,0,,上帝啊 等等!\N{\rEng}Jesus, dude!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.98,0:18:52.92,Chn,,0,0,0,,嘿, 看见Kyle了吗?\N{\rEng}Hey, kid, have you seen Kyle?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.95,0:18:55.39,Chn,,0,0,0,,我们找他有急事 但那都找不到他\N{\rEng}We've looked everywhere and we have to show him something.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.35,0:18:59.72,Chn,,0,0,0,,他去烧学校了 - 什么?\N{\rEng}He's burning down the school. - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.75,0:19:02.68,Chn,,0,0,0,,他说他要去把学校夷为平地\N{\rEng}He said he gonna burn the school down to the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.49,0:19:12.62,Chn,,0,0,0,,所有的鄙视和嘲笑终要结束!\N{\rEng}All the cruel jokes and ridicule will finally be over!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.65,0:19:16.32,Chn,,0,0,0,,现在你高兴了吧 God?! 你让我长成这样!\N{\rEng}Are you happy now, God?! You made me look like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.35,0:19:19.63,Chn,,0,0,0,,Kyle! Kyle 别! - 不要阻止我 Stan!\N{\rEng}Kyle! Kyle, don't! - Don't try and stop me, Stan!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.66,0:19:22.54,Chn,,0,0,0,,你根本不理解被人当作畸形怪物的感觉!\N{\rEng}You don't know how it feels to be a deformed monstrosity!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.57,0:19:24.84,Chn,,0,0,0,,排名是伪造的, Kyle!\N{\rEng}The list was a forgery, Kyle!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.89,0:19:29.21,Chn,,0,0,0,,不是女生们的真实投票 我们找到了真正的排名\N{\rEng}It didn't sparkle with all the girls. We have the real list.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.15,0:19:34.10,Chn,,0,0,0,,够了! 把名单给我 Wendy!\N{\rEng}That's about far enough! Give me that list, Wendy!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.15,0:19:37.28,Chn,,0,0,0,,Stan 究竟是怎么回事?! - 是因为鞋子 Kyle.\N{\rEng}Stan, what is going on?! - It was about shoes, Kyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.31,0:19:39.31,Chn,,0,0,0,,女生们想要鞋子 所以他们利用你\N{\rEng}The girls wanted shoes, so they set you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.34,0:19:41.31,Chn,,0,0,0,,Kyle只是个牺牲品!\N{\rEng}Kyle was simple a casualty!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.34,0:19:44.23,Chn,,0,0,0,,要提升Clyde 必须把 Craig 调到第12\N{\rEng}To move Clyde meant that Craig has to be moved to number twelve,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.23,0:19:47.32,Chn,,0,0,0,,把Jimmy下调 把Jason提升 !\N{\rEng}which moved Jimmy down and moved Jason up!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.35,0:19:49.00,Chn,,0,0,0,,那我究竟是第几?\N{\rEng}So what number was I?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.03,0:19:52.25,Chn,,0,0,0,,你把一切都弄乱了! 我们的排名应该是真实的!\N{\rEng}You've compromised everything! Our list's integrity!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.28,0:19:55.44,Chn,,0,0,0,,看看这些鞋子 Wendy?! 它们太不可思议了!\N{\rEng}Did you see these shoes, Wendy?! They're incredible!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.47,0:19:57.91,Chn,,0,0,0,,这不是多不可思议的问题 你不能-\N{\rEng}It doesn't matter how incredible they are. You can't-
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.91,0:20:00.89,Chn,,0,0,0,,Oh My God 这鞋太炫了 - 是吧?\N{\rEng}Oh my God, those are amazing. - Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.92,0:20:03.75,Chn,,0,0,0,,上边那是蕾丝边么? - 不，那是小鞋带\N{\rEng}Is that a lace across the top? - No, it's a little strap.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.78,0:20:07.59,Chn,,0,0,0,,- 但这不是理由!你太过分了!\N{\rEng}Wendy? Wendy? - But it doesn't matter. You took it too far!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.62,0:20:11.19,Chn,,0,0,0,,要不是你玩柯南游戏 事情早就过去了!\N{\rEng}If you hadn't gone all Nancy Drew on us, this would have just gone away!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.22,0:20:13.96,Chn,,0,0,0,,她要杀了我们? - 太迟了 Bebe.\N{\rEng}She's gonna kill us? - It's too late, Bebe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.98,0:20:17.90,Chn,,0,0,0,,我已经写了个报告交给警察局了 真相会大白的\N{\rEng}I've already made a full report and sent a copy to the police. People will know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.93,0:20:20.15,Chn,,0,0,0,,得了吧  吓唬谁啊\N{\rEng}Oh please, you're lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.31,0:20:29.42,Chn,,0,0,0,,投降吧 Bebe. 我们全都知道了 排名是伪造的\N{\rEng}Give it up, Bebe. We know all about it. The list was compromised.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.45,0:20:33.13,Chn,,0,0,0,,Kyle Broflovski 不是班上最丑的男生\N{\rEng}Kyle Broflovski is not the ugliest boy in the class.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.47,0:20:41.49,Chn,,0,0,0,,Wendy!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.63,0:21:02.91,Chn,,0,0,0,,等等，我什么都没干 - 到局子里再解释吧\N{\rEng}Wait, I didn't do anything wrong. - You can explain all that downtown.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.94,0:21:04.18,Chn,,0,0,0,,给\N{\rEng}Here, Kyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.21,0:21:08.43,Chn,,0,0,0,,咱们都经历了一些事 但是 现在你可以知道自己到底是第几了\N{\rEng}We've been through a lot, but, you can finally see where you really are on the list.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.11,0:21:18.98,Chn,,0,0,0,,你确定这样就没事了 Kyle? - 确定。 林肯是对的\N{\rEng}Are you sure you're okay with this, Kyle? - I'm sure. Abe Lincoln was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.01,0:21:23.15,Chn,,0,0,0,,我可不想知道自己很帅 然后长大之后变成一个弱智\N{\rEng}I don't wanna find out I'm good-looking and become a total shithead when I grow up.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.34,0:21:24.61,Chn,,0,0,0,,林肯?\N{\rEng}Abe Lincoln?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.70,0:21:27.48,Chn,,0,0,0,,Stan 能我很高兴能跟你和好\N{\rEng}Stan, it's been really great hanging out with you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.51,0:21:31.41,Chn,,0,0,0,,我觉得你好像变了 变得好厉害\N{\rEng}I feel like you've changed somehow. In a really awesome way.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.44,0:21:35.55,Chn,,0,0,0,,嗯  事情总会变的 不是么?\N{\rEng}Yeah well, I guess a lot of things change, don't they?